# Ai_Projects

A collection of small to medium AI/ML-focused Python projects located under `Ai_Projects/` in this repository.

## Overview
This folder groups experiments, demos, and learning projects related to Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, and automation. Projects are intended to be simple and self-contained so you can run them locally, study the code, and adapt them.

## Prerequisites
- **Python:** 3.9+ recommended
- **pip:** recent version
- (Recommended) **venv** / **virtualenv** for isolated environments

> Some projects may require extra system dependencies (e.g., `ffmpeg`, `tesseract`, GPU drivers). Check each project’s `requirements.txt` and documentation.

## Quick start

```bash
# Clone
git clone https://github.com/RitikChoudhary01/python-projects.git
cd python-projects

# Create & activate a virtual environment
python -m venv .venv
# Windows
.venv\Scripts\activate
# macOS/Linux
source .venv/bin/activate
```

## Install dependencies
Dependencies can be either shared at the repo root or per-project.

```bash
# Option A: install shared requirements (if present)
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Option B: install per-project requirements (recommended, if present)
pip install -r Ai_Projects/<project_name>/requirements.txt
```

## Run a project

```bash
cd Ai_Projects/<project_name>
python main.py
```

If the project is a single script, it might be:

```bash
python <script_name>.py
```

If it’s notebook-based:

```bash
pip install notebook
jupyter notebook
```

## Suggested folder structure

```text
Ai_Projects/
  <project_1>/
    README.md
    requirements.txt
    main.py
    src/
    data/
  <project_2>/
    ...
```

